      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Eugenicists often cited studies that measured the supposed physical and mental differences between racial groups. One notable example is the work of Francis Galton, who claimed that the average cranial capacity of non-whites was significantly smaller than that of whites. He based his findings on a series of measurements taken from skulls, which he claimed showed a clear correlation between skull size and intelligence. Galton's work was later discredited, but it was widely cited by eugenicists to support their claims of racial superiority.",
